The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 19: The cabinet committee on economic affairs will meet here tomorrow to discuss increase in petrol and diesel prices against the backdrop of Left parties? strong opposition to any move on this front. The cabinet had last Thursday informally agreed on the need to raise petrol and diesel prices but a decision was not taken pending Left parties approval, finance ministry sources said.

 Calcutta, June 19: Coal India Ltd will float global tenders to develop three mines under its subsidiary, Mahanadi Coalfields Ltd, which together would have a production capacity of 23.5 million tonnes. The three mines are Kulda, Bhubaneswari and Kaniha. ?Coal India will only be responsible for safety and infrastructure development,? sources here said.

 Mumbai, June 19: Larsen and Toubro (L amp;T) Infotech will spend Rs 300-crore to fund its expansion plans. This includes setting up four software development centres. The centres will come up in Powai, Mahape (Navi Mumbai), Chennai and Bangalore.

 New Delhi, June 19: The government has given its go-ahead to three special economic zones (SEZs), one each in Gujarat, Haryana and Karnataka. Gujarat Industrial Development Corporation proposes to set up an apparel park in Surat. The Bangalore SEZ will cater to telecom and it sectors.

 New Delhi, June 19: The government has appointed new executive directors to Punjab National Bank, Bank of Baroda, Bank of India, Corporation Bank, Oriental Bank of Commerce, United Bank of India and Dena Bank. 

 New Delhi, June 19: The Jufeyr oilfield, one of the two fields that Iran offered to Ongc Videsh Ltd (OVL) in lieu of India buying $22-billion worth of liquefied natural gas, may be a depleted field.

 New Delhi, June 19: Assocham has favoured the repeal of urban land ceiling act and rationalising property tax across the country. The chamber feels this would attract multinationals into the retail sector and have a multiplier effect on the agriculture, manufacturing and food processing sectors.




